windowToggleSelect(25.10)                            windowToggleSelect(25.10)

Name
       windowToggleSelect  -  Toggles between selecting or deselecting objects
       that are enclosed by the area defined by the coordinates

Syntax
       windowToggleSelect

       [-help]

       <x1><y1><x2><y2>

       Toggles between selecting or deselecting objects that are  enclosed  by
       the area defined by the coordinates. Use this command to select or des-
       elect all objects within a specific area.

       Note: This command works only in GUI mode.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each windowToggleSelect parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man windowToggleSelect

       <x1> <y1> <x2> <y2>
              Specifies  the coordinates of the window area to enclose the ob-
              jects to be selected or deselected.

Example
       The first command selects the objects that are totally enclosed by  the
       area with coordinates defined as (x1=10, y1=200) and (x2=100, y2=50):

       The  second  command deselects the objects that are totally enclosed by
       the same area:

       windowToggleSelect 10 200 100 50

       windowToggleSelect 10 200 100 50

